      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative agreement metric defined a priori; FEA predictions within acceptance band for primary QoI",
      "rationale": "Primary QoI is construct stiffness (N/mm) under ASTM F1717 compression-bending. Acceptance criterion: FEA ensemble mean within +/-15% of experimental mean. Achieved: ensemble mean 1842 N/mm vs. experimental mean 1798 N/mm (2.4% difference). All 11 specimen-specific predictions within acceptance band."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validated QoI directly linked to clinical performance metric or regulatory submission requirement",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness and peak screw shank stress are the QoIs. Stiffness directly corresponds to the ASTM F1717 regulatory submission metric. Peak stress informs fatigue life prediction relevant to clinical failure mode. Both QoIs are mechanistically linked to the intended use of the model."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation scenario geometry, material, loading, and boundary conditions match COU within documented tolerances",
      "rationale": "Validation specimens are production-representative non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screws tested under ASTM F1717 compression-bending, which is the exact regulatory test the FEA model is intended to support. Geometry, material, and loading are directly equivalent to the COU. Relevance is high."
    }
